condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Attachment to Annex to Schedule 2, 3(a) | Description :The Borrower shall submit to the Bank for its priorapproval 1st 2 Sub-loans by the Borrower and each PB and each Sub-loan which isrequired to be presented to the Bank for priorapproval in OM. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Attachment to Annex to Schedule 2, 5 | Description :A Sub-loan may be made for an EE Sub-Project which isdetermined on the basis of an appraisal carried out in accordance with procedures acceptable to the Bank set forth in the OM. |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Attachment to Annex to Schedule 2, 6 | Description :Sub-loans may finance working capital up to an aggregateamount not to exceed 10% of the Sub-loan, provided that such working capital is used solely for the purposes of EE Sub-Projects. |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A1 | Description :The Borrower shall maintain the PIU until completion of the Project andshall ensure that the PIU functions satisfactorily at all times and with necessary staffing and budgetary resources. | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A4 (a) | Description :The Borrower shall select for direct on-lending Energy Efficiency(EE) Sub-Projects which meet the criteria set forth in the Operations Manual (OM). | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A4 (b) | Description :The Borrower shall select Participating Banks (PBs) pursuant tocriteria set forth in paragraph A.1 of the Annex to Schedule 2. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, C | Description :The Borrower shall carry out the Project in compliance with theEnvironmental Assessment Framework and shall ensure each Sub-Project's compliance with environmental review procedures set in OM. |Frequency :Yearly
